<h2 id="sec-1"><span class="section-number-2">1</span> Simplifying NAND gates</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-1">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-sec-1-1" class="outline-3 learn">
<h3 id="sec-1-1">Learn It</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>NAND gates are really useful, but it would be annoying to have to draw the transistors every time.
</li>
<li>Instead we use a symbol like the one shown below. You can click the buttons and compare it to the transistor version below it, to see that they are identical in function.
</li>
</ul>
<object data="js/NAND.html" width='200px' height='200px'></object>
<hr  />
<object data="js/TranNAND.html" width='300px' height='320px'></object>
</div>
