<div id="outline-container-sec-4" class="outline-2 activity">
<h2 id="sec-4"><span class="section-number-2">4</span> Making other gates from NAND gates.</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-4">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>We've already seen one other gate that can be made using NAND gates - it was called an AND gate.
</li>
<li>Below is the diagram for the NAND gate arrangements for an AND gate again, and a simplified symbol for an AND gate that is commonly used.
</li>
</ul>
<object data="js/ANDfromNANDS.html" width='300px' height='100px'></object>
<object data="js/AND.html" width='200px' height='100px'></object>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Hopefully you can see that the two are identical. When inputs A and B are on, output Q is on. When either or both A and B are off, Q is off.
</li>
<li>The AND gate has a very similar symbol to the NAND gate (it's just missing the little circle near the output) so make sure you don't get the two confused.
</li>
<li>The truth table for an AND gate looks like this
</li>
</ul>
<table border="2" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="6" rules="groups" frame="hsides">


